&lt;p&gt;Fellview Healthcare Limited is a large practice based in West Cumbria primarily in and around the towns of Whitehaven and Egremont.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate over four sites – Flatt Walks (Whitehaven), Beech House (Egremont), Cleator Moor Health Centre (Cleator Moor) and Griffin Close (Frizington).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a combined list size of 23,200 patients and provide a wide range of services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a strong clinical team of GP’s, Nurse Practitioners and Community Nurse Practitioners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a training practice, high QOF achievers with a strong primary health care team to provide high quality care. We are forward thinking, innovative and our recent CQC visit (November 2015) rated the practice outstanding in two areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for permanent GP’s or those wishing to work as salaried GP’s.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;GP’S – FULL-TIME&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;8 Sessions per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Six Weeks Holiday per Annum*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One Week Study leave per Annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Pro-rate dependent on number of sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;SALARIED GP - WTE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;8 Sessions per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Six Weeks Holiday per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One Week Study leave per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Pro-rate dependent on number of sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;FULL-TIME GP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;8 Sessions per week (usually over four days)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;16 patients per session (10 minute appointments)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Share of Home Visits (usually 1-2day)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Share of paperwork (electronic/paper scripts/investigations/documents)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One day triage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Attendance at primary health care team meetings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Attendance at PLT training days&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;SALARIED GP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties/responsibility will be dependent upon number of sessions worked and will be done pro-rata.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more details please contact Mark Megan via e-mail: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mark.megan@gp-a82044.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date for applications: 31st March 2021&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
